stealing lots of stuff from http://www.universalmind.com/blog/technology/smoking-meat-with-the-internet-of-things/
and https://learn.adafruit.com/thermistor/using-a-thermistor

will have a meat_probe and a grill_probe

need to figure out the beta-coefficient of the thermistor

Use this library for writing to the oled
    https://github.com/squix78/esp8266-oled-ssd1306

here's how to "multiplex" two analog inputs
    https://hackaday.io/project/8435-2-analog-inputs-for-esp8266-without-multiplexer

probe info
    https://github.com/CapnBry/HeaterMeter/wiki/HeaterMeter-Probes

using sparkfun for http data upload
    public url
        https://data.sparkfun.com/streams/RM4KV6gqxWcGv5gwvgnb
    public key
        RM4KV6gqxWcGv5gwvgnb
    private key
        lzNeK5qpEkCeyKrByrvY
    logging format
        http://data.sparkfun.com/input/[publicKey]?private_key=[privateKey]&grilltemp=[value]
    logging example
        https://data.sparkfun.com/input/RM4KV6gqxWcGv5gwvgnb?private_key=lzNeK5qpEkCeyKrByrvY&grilltemp=29.70
